<TEXT>
 the espionage trial of u.s. businessman edmund pope is under way in moscow.
 according to his lawyer, pope is refusing to participate until he is removed
 from the six-man cell where he is being held.
 the former naval intelligence officer has been diagnosed with bone cancer.
 pope's lawyer says the other men in his cell smoke which endangers his health.
 he has been in detention for seven months.
 russia says pope tried to buy secret design information on a silent torpedo.
 pope's lawyer denies the allegation.
